title: Miracles few and far between as search for life after earthquake becomes bid to honour dead
description: The miracles are becoming few and far between - the search for life is now a bid to honour the dead.

title: Dozens of flights cancelled as New Zealand braces for cyclone
description: Dozens of flights to and from New Zealand have been cancelled as the country braces for its second severe storm in a matter of weeks.

title: US military shoots down another unidentified flying object
description: The US military has shot down another unidentified flying object - this time over Lake Huron in Michigan.

title: Still 'much to know' about unidentified object shot down over Canada, says Trudeau
description: Recovery teams are searching for the unidentified cylindrical object shot down over Canada to work out what its purpose was, the country's Prime Minister Justin Trudeau has said.

title: Allowing Russian athletes to compete 'doing more for peace', says Olympic chief
description: International Olympic chief Thomas Bach has insisted the organisation is "doing more for peace" in seeking to allow athletes from Russia and Belarus to compete at next year's Paris Games.

title: 'Open and shut case' for more Syria crossings to boost earthquake relief effort, says UN aid boss
description: Providing extra border crossings from Turkey into Syria is an "open and shut case" on humanitarian grounds following the catastrophic "mega" disaster, a UN aid chief has told Sky News.

title: Boy, nine, pulled out alive after five days underground in arms of his mother
description: In the wasteland that scars the centre of Kahramanmaras in Turkey, we watched a pair of rescuers perched in a digger's scoop as they investigated a great pile of concrete.

title: 'Reports of clashes' prompt some aid organisations to pause quake rescue work in Turkey
description: Aid workers in Turkey say the security situation is deteriorating, leaving them struggling to help those affected by the recent earthquake.
